{%- doc -%}
  Customer account dashboard (classic accounts). Thin driver: resolves the
  customer's tier + autoship state, then renders snippets/customer-dashboard,
  which shifts blocks per state (VIP / Elite / Free no-autoship / Free cancelled).

  Data: tier + credits = native (Inveterate tags + metafield). Autoship state is
  a placeholder until the Stay AI worker ships — replace `real_autoship` below.
{%- enddoc -%}
{%- liquid
  capture membership_tier
    render 'customer-membership-tier'
  endcapture
  assign membership_tier = membership_tier | strip
  assign real_tier = membership_tier | default: 'FREE'

  # "YOUR CREDIT" = redeemable store credits (inveterate.balance) — what the member can redeem NOW,
  # which the credit-expiry (worker) refers to. The Inveterate metafield stores a DECIMAL DOLLAR
  # amount (e.g. 2120.0 = $2,120), but Shopify's `money` filter expects cents — so multiply by 100
  # before formatting (the account worker does the same ×100 to build balance_formatted).
  assign credit_balance = customer.metafields.inveterate.balance | default: 0
  assign credits_formatted = credit_balance | times: 100 | money_without_trailing_zeros

  # TODO worker (/apps/wb/subscriptions): real autoship state (none|active|cancelled).
  # Mock: members have an active autoship, FREE has none.
  assign real_autoship = 'none'
  unless real_tier == 'FREE'
    assign real_autoship = 'active'
  endunless
-%}

<section class="w-full" style="background-color: var(--color-brand-beige);">
  {%- comment -%}
    data-wb-account marks the hydration root; account.ts fetches the worker summary
    and fills the SSR cards with worker data (progress / autoship / expiry). Tier name
    and credit balance stay SSR-native (Inveterate tags + metafield) to avoid flicker.
    - data-worker-url: theme setting settings.account_worker_url. When set → account.ts
      calls {url}/dev/<path>?customerId= directly; when EMPTY → signed App Proxy /apps/wb.
    - data-customer-id: passed to the /dev endpoint (App Proxy injects the signed
      logged_in_customer_id itself, so it is ignored on the /apps/wb path).
    - data-wb-loading: initial state; account.ts removes it on success, sets
      data-wb-error on failure (SSR fallback values remain).
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="account-container py-8 md:!py-12"
       data-wb-account
       data-wb-loading
       data-worker-url="{{ settings.account_worker_url | default: '' }}"
       data-worker-token="{{ settings.account_worker_dev_token | default: '' }}"
       data-customer-id="{{ customer.id }}"
       data-wb-portal-url="{{ settings.manage_autoship_url | default: '/apps/retextion' }}">
    {%- render 'customer-dashboard', tier: real_tier, autoship_state: real_autoship, credits_formatted: credits_formatted -%}
  </div>
  {%- render 'vite-tag' with 'account.ts' -%}
</section>
